sql:
SELECT log_device, COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS active_user_count
FROM user_activity_logs
GROUP BY log_device;

SELECT AVG(average_session_duration)
FROM data_reports
WHERE month = 'May' AND year = 2023;

SELECT AVG(LENGTH(policy_text))
FROM privacy_policies
WHERE policy_status = 'active';

external_knowledge:
User number 1 refers to the specific identifier for a user in the user_accounts table; 
Cookie acceptance implies that the user has agreed to the cookie's usage as per the privacy policy linked to their client; 
In this context, 'accepted cookies' means those with 'is_accepted' set to 1.

sql:
SELECT c.name, c.description, c.same_site, c.secure_flag, c.http_only_flag, cc.consent_date, cc.is_accepted, cc.consent_expiration_date, cc.consent_ip_address, cc.consent_device
FROM cookies c
INNER JOIN cookie_consent cc ON c.cookie_id = cc.cookie_id;
